description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a locum Consultant in HIV and Sexual health to join our committed team in HIV medicine and Sexual health. The post is 8.5 PA’s and for a fixed term of 8 months with a possibility to extend to 12 months to start as soon as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be based primarily at the North Middlesex hospital providing HIV inpatient and outpatient care and also deliver sexual health clinics in the community. The post holder will be expected to have broad experience in all aspects of Genito-Urinary Medicine and HIV medicine, and provide clinical supervision to junior medical colleagues and the nursing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will lead on supervision of trainees in the HIV service as well as on HIV/Sexual health primary prevention. He/she will contribute to quality improvement and development of services, training and governance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The job plan involves 1:3 on-call rota for HIV emergencies and advice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To discuss the post, candidates are invited to contact Dr Wai Ching Loke Clinical Director in HIV and Sexual Health waiching.loke@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Wai Ching LokeJob titleClinical Director, HIV and Community Sexual Health ServicesEmail addresswaiching.loke@nhs.netTelephone number0208 887 4501/3236&lt;/p&gt;
